workout_description:
AMRAP in 10 minutes of:
30 double-unders
15 power snatches (75/55 lb)

Complete as many rounds and reps as possible in 15 minutes of:
9 Deadlifts 155/100
12 Push-ups
15 Box jumps 24"/20"

Complete as many rounds and reps as possible in 5 minutes of:
Squat clean 165/110
Jerk 165/110

Complete as many rounds and reps as possible in 10 minutes of:
60 Bar-facing burpees
30 Overhead squats 120/40 lbs
10 Muscle-ups

Complete as many rounds and reps as possible in 20 minutes of:
5 Power cleans 145/100 lbs
10 Toes to bar
15 Wall balls 20/14 lbs
Men - Target 10'
Women - Target 9'

AMRAP in 7 minutes:
3 thrusters 100/65 lb
3 chest-to-bar pull-ups
6 thrusters 100/65 lb
6 chest-to-bar pull-ups
9 thrusters 100/65 lb
9 chest-to-bar pull-ups
If you complete the round of 9, complete a round of 12, then go on to 15, etc.

AMRAP in 7 minutes:
Burpees to a target (6 inch)

Proceed through the sequence below completing as many reps as possible in 10 minutes of:
Snatch, 30 reps 45/75 lbs
Snatch, 30 reps 75/135 lbs
Snatch, 30 reps 100/165 lbs
Snatch, as many reps as possible 120/210 lbs

Complete as many rounds and reps as possible in 18 minutes of:
15 Box jumps 24"/20" 
12 Push press 115/75 
9 Toes-to-bar

Complete as many rounds and reps as possible in 12 minutes of:
150 Wall balls (20 lbs to 10' target) (14 lbs to 9' target)
90 Double-unders
30 Muscle-ups

Complete as many reps as possible in 7 minutes following the rep scheme below:
3 Thruster 75/100 lbs 
3 Chest to bar Pull-ups
6 Thruster 75/100 lbs 
6 Chest to bar Pull-ups
9 Thruster 75/100 lbs 
9 Chest to bar Pull-ups
12 Thruster 75/100 lbs 
12 Chest to bar Pull-ups
15 Thruster 75/100 lbs 
15 Chest to bar Pull-ups
18 Thruster 75/100 lbs 
18 Chest to bar Pull-ups
21 Thruster 75/100 lbs 
21 Chest to bar Pull-ups...
This is a timed workout. If you complete the round of 21, go on to 24. If you complete 24, go on to 27, etc.

AMRAP in 17 minutes:
40 burpees
30 snatches (75/45 lb)
30 burpees
30 snatches (135/75 lb)
20 burpees
30 snatches (165/100 lb)
10 burpees
Max snatches (210/120 lb)

AMRAP in 10 minutes:
5 shoulder-to-overheads (115/75 lb)
10 deadlifts (115/75 lb)
15 box jumps (24/20 inch)

AMRAP in 12 minutes:
150 wall balls
90 double-unders
30 muscle-ups

AMRAP in 7 minutes:
3 clean-and-jerks (135/95 lb)
3 toes-to-bars
6 clean-and-jerks (135/95 lb)
6 toes-to-bars
9 clean-and-jerks (135/95 lb)
9 toes-to-bars
12 clean-and-jerks (135/95 lb)
12 toes-to-bars

If athlete completes the round of 12, go on to 15. Complete 15, go on to 18, etc.

AMRAP for as long as possible:
15 thrusters (100/65 lb)
15 chest-to-bar pull-ups

If 90 reps (3 rounds) are completed in under 4 minutes, time extends to 8 minutes.
If 180 reps (6 rounds) are completed in under 8 minutes, time extends to 12 minutes. Etc.

Complete as many rounds and reps as possible in 10 minutes of:
30 double-unders
power snatches, 15 reps (75 lb/55 lb)

From 0:00-3:00, perform 2 rounds of:
10 overhead squats (95/65 lb)
10 chest-to-bar pull-ups
From 3:00-6:00, perform 2 rounds of:
12 overhead squats (95/65 lb)
12 chest-to-bar pull-ups
From 6:00-9:00, perform 2 rounds of:
14 overhead squats (95/65 lb)
14 chest-to-bar pull-ups
Follow the pattern, adding 2 reps to each exercise every 3 minutes, until you fail to complete both rounds within the 3-minute interval.

AMRAP in 8 minutes of:
10 deadlifts (135/95 lb)
15 box jumps (24/20 inch)
15 deadlifts (185/135 lb)
15 box jumps (24/20 inch)
20 deadlifts (225/155 lb)
15 box jumps (24/20 inch)
25 deadlifts (275/185 lb)
15 box jumps (24/20 inch)
30 deadlifts (315/205 lb)
15 box jumps (24/20 inch)
35 deadlifts (365/225 lb)
15 box jumps (24/20 inch)

AMRAP in 14 minutes of:
60 calorie row
50 toes-to-bars
40 wall ball shots (20/14 lb, 10/9 ft)
30 cleans (135 lb)
20 muscle-ups

21-18-15-12-9-6-3 reps for time:
Thrusters (95/65 lb)
Bar facing burpees

Two parts in 15 minutes
15.1 AMRAP in 9 minutes
15 toes-to-bars
10 deadlifts
5 snatches

Then, 15.1a, from 9:00-15:00
1 rep max clean-and-jerk

From 0:00-3:00
2 rounds of:
10 overhead squats (95 / 65 lb.)
10 chest-to-bar pull-ups

From 3:00-6:00
2 rounds of:
12 overhead squats (95 / 65 lb.)
12 chest-to-bar pull-ups

From 6:00-9:00
2 rounds of:
14 overhead squats (95 / 65 lb.)
14 chest-to-bar pull-ups
Etc., following the same pattern
until you fail to complete both
rounds

Complete as many rounds and repetitions as possible in 14 minutes of:
 
7 muscle-ups
50 wall-ball shots
100 double-unders

Men use 20-lb. ball to 10 feet, Women use 14-lb.
ball to 9 feet

AMRAP in 8 minutes:
3 handstand push-ups, 3 cleans (185/125 lb)
6 handstand push-ups, 3 cleans (185/125 lb)
9 handstand push-ups, 3 cleans (185/125 lb)
12 handstand push-ups, 6 cleans (185/125 lb)
15 handstand push-ups, 6 cleans (185/125 lb)
18 handstand push-ups, 6 cleans (185/125 lb)
21 handstand push-ups, 9 cleans (185/125 lb)
...
Continue with the pattern, adding 3 handstand push-ups to each round and 3 cleans to every third round

27-21-15-9 reps for time:
Calorie row
Thrusters (95/65 lb)

AMRAP in 20 minutes:
25 ft overhead walking lunges (95/65 lb)
8 bar facing burpees
25 ft overhead walking lunges (95/65 lb)
8 chest-to-bar pull-ups

AMRAP in 20 minutes:

50 double-unders

50 double-unders

25 toes-to-bars
50 double-unders

Complete as many rounds and reps as possible in 7 minutes of:
10 power snatches
3 bar muscle-ups

Men use 75 lb.
Women use 55 lb.
